[5] Shigellosis - USA (Texas)
Date: Sat 26 Jun 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: News 9 San Antonio [edited]
<http://news9sanantonio.com/content/top_stories/default.asp?ArID=12846>

The San Antonio Metropolitan Health District has noticed a big spike in
cases of shigellosis over the past 6 months, especially among children.
Experts said that people catch shigellosis by not washing their hands, and
doctors said that the best way to avoid getting sick is basic hygiene.
"The best way to prevent the infection is going to be frequent handwashing,
especially when someone in the household is ill or when someone is caring
for a small child, whether it is in a day care setting or home. Handwashing
after every diaper change, and before meal preparation, is essential,"
Cantu said.
Records show that in May 2004, there were 100 cases of shigellosis in the
county; most were in day care centers. In June 2004, only 33 cases have
been reported so far.
